# Spiderman
Peter Parker, or Spider-Man, is an American Marvel Comics superhero created by writer Stan Lee and artist Steve Ditko, who debuted in Amazing Fantasy #15 (August 1962) and, because of his popularity, began to have a one-shot comic featuring A few months later, he began to have one-shot comics featuring himself. Spider-Man, whose full name is Peter Benjamin Parker, is an ordinary American student who graduates and becomes a journalist for the Daily Bugle. After being accidentally bitten by a radioactively infected spider, he gains the same superpowers, superhuman stamina, reflexes, agility and speed as the spider. He invented a spider web launcher and has since taken on the guardianship of New York as Spider-Man.
